 It was a special day for Nyasie Odundo as she walked down the aisle to start her new life with boyfriend Eric Ngwiri. The lovebirds took their marriage vows at the Lavington United Church in Nairobi on Saturday. The groom is the head of the strategic advisory service at Kimetrica Ltd while the bride works in the human resources field. The newlyweds are the children of two former Nation Media Group editors; the bride is the daughter of former NMG editorial director Joseph Odindo while the groom is the son of Magesha Ngwiri, who is a former opinion editor at the Nation. After their vows, the newlyweds hosted a reception for their family and friends at the Arboretum Gardens.